From 7f64d0f12ec7fd9e8f137496f74ce18dadde9890 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jun 2025 16:30:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add minimum PSD calculation
 with puncture mask support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add get_min_psd_values(), a helper function that calculates the minimum
Power Spectral Density (PSD) values for a given frequency and bandwidth in the
6 GHz band. This function integrates all previously introduced logic for
puncture mask shaping and regulatory mask computation to ensure compliance with
Out-of-Band Emission (OOBE) constraints.

The function begins by validating the Automated Frequency Coordination (AFC)
response structure and extracting the frequency object list. It then determines
the puncture type and populates the corresponding puncture mask structures
using get_puncture_type_and_masks(). For each frequency in the range of ±3 times
the channel bandwidth around the center frequency, it retrieves the PSD limit
using get_psd_limit(). It then computes the regulatory mask using get_regmask(),
which internally selects the more restrictive value between punctured and
non-punctured masks. The minimum PSD value is updated by subtracting the scaled
regulatory mask from the PSD limit.

Finalize the encapsulation of all internal helpers by marking them static. These
include get_psd_limit(), get_y_val(), get_regmask_non_puncture(),
handle_edge_puncture(), handle_interim_20_plus(), handle_interim_20(),
get_puncture_type_and_masks(), and get_regmask(). Only get_min_psd_values()
remains globally visible, as it serves as the primary interface for computing
PSD constraints in the presence of puncturing.

Update ieee802_11.h to remove declarations for internal helpers and expose only
get_min_psd_values(). This ensures a clean and minimal interface while
preserving modularity and testability.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
